race.comment: Lots of win chances. ZOUBELLE (12) has been going better than last couple suggest and will find this much easier. Close-up third at Sandown two back then found the class a bit much at Cranbourne latest. This suits and worth another try. MONTJUIC MAGIC (8) was on speed and narrowly beaten at Cranbourne two back then ridden quietly when safely held there last time. Back in grade and did win only try course and distance. MONT SAINT MICHEL (4) has been racing over further and winding up late and will no doubt spot a start again over the sharper trip. Best figures measure up though and drawn for a soft run with cover. Will explode late. JUICE BOX (2) has a great record this circuit with three wins and two minors from five tries. Speedy mare who will take catching. SWEET 'N' SPICY (10) ran seventh at Cranbourne latest but wasn't far away and will find this much easier. Hard to hold out late.
